Sunshine Co. is the perfect brunch spot. We drove from Philly for a day in the city and randomly stumbled across this gem. The drinks, food and service was amazing. The outdoor dining setup was perfect to ensure customers social distanced.

I love this restaurant and have been going here regularly for many years. I have never had a negative experience and the food has always been superb. Everyone is warm and friendly and the music is excellent. The standards have not fallen AT ALL since the pandemic, the sheer thought of the watermelon and feta salad is making me drool right now. Disappointed would be an understatement for our experience here. Firstly, we where treated by the staff as if they where doing us a favor by being there, and we where “greeted” with a massive attitude to begin with but because the food looked good we decided to stay. There was ZERO effort to check on any of the tables, they for what ever reason took my drink order and didn’t bother to wait and hear what my boyfriend wanted. When we wanted to order more drinks we practically had to track a waiter down to get any attention.  Secondly, the food was average at best. It was presented beautifully, but completely lacked flavor.  This was such a disappointment and I could tell all other tables felt the same way too. Such a shame as we where willing to spend a lot of money.

Sunshine Co has one of the best atmospheres of any restaurant I’ve been to in NYC. The style is French bistro and old school speakeasy-esque, casual but elegant. The music is great and the perfect volume, the service is fantastic, and the food is top notch. I’ve been here 10+ times in the past three years and it has never faltered; for brunch or dinner. Everyone in my party always enjoys their meals as much if not more than I. It’s easy to get lost in the slough of great restaurants in prospect heights, but this should not be missed.

Love this place, come to brunch very often. Gets crowded but that's because it's so good. Often a 20 minute wait for a table at brunch, but don't let that deter you. I always order eggs benedict or salmon eggs benedict, those have never disappointed me. Took a bite of the brussels sprout hash my friend ordered, was very pleasantly surprised--it's delicious, even though I'm typically not a fan of brussels sprouts. They also have some really great cocktails--five petals is my personal favorite. And they're very reasonably priced! Definitely check them out.

Sunshine is on the corner of the street we live on, so my husband and I come in often - mostly for brunch. It’s a wonderful, warm place - and we feel really lucky to be locals and regulars!  The staff is incredible. Their bartenders, servers, and host have all been there for a really long time, and they’re all amazing.  One of our favorite brunch cocktails (The Five Petals) uses an egg-white merengue - which requires a tremendous amount of shaking and takes serious skill to get perfectly cloud-like - and these guys nail it every time no matter which bartender makes it.  Also recommend the apricot sausage - sooo good! It comes 3 small patties to an order, and it’s the perfect sweet/savory balance.  Inside it’s a a mix of high-top tables in the front, a good amount of seating at the bar,  and booth-seating with larger tables toward the back. In the summertime, their outdoor seating is perfect for people watching, and/or having lunch with your dog.  It’s a wonderful place, with really good food, run by awesome people.  Highly recommend!

Delicious place with solid entrees and apps, and a stellar list of classic and special cocktails. Popular for brunch, nice spot to hit for a quick bar, and good value for the menu. Unfortunately I would have to say the B or C team was on in the kitchen.  Flavorless mushroom flat bread, odd toppings on the crostini, and I don't know what the that other dish was, but it certainly wasn't Bolognese!  The trout was very tasty and the lentils were delicious although I'm not sure why they were together because the lentils were more wet like a soup or stewoup instead of dryer like a rice. Drinks were good and had great ice cubes! I hope they work it out. I really like this place otherwise.

My husband and I were hungry and in the Prospect Heights area. After a quick yelp search we decided on Sunshine as there were such glowing reviews. Each persons review is of course about their experience. Ours, that Sunday was relatively 1.5-2 stars.  We walked in and were immediately seated at a table so close to the door that it almost felt like people were going to open the door right into us. We get menus, coffee and water and place an order of steak n eggs and french toast.  While waiting for our order, a party of 5 came in and asked if they could sit at the table next to us which is for 4 people. The waitstaff said sure and brought them an extra chair and placed it so close to our table every time she moved our table shook. It was absolutely ridiculous. Instead of telling them to wait for a table to open up, they kept staring at us hoping we'd offer to move tables so they can use ours as a table for 6. We felt so uncomfortable, we of course got the hint and moved to a different less comfortable table.  Our food came, the steak was the size of my palm (I have a small hand), could have been eaten in one bite. For $16, that's totally unreasonable. The french toast was pretty mediocre and bland, really nothing to write home about.  My overall thoughts about Sunshine is that the establishment and vibe is pretty pretentious and not a place I'd want to dine at again.

Last night I got together with a group of friends and we ran across this restaurant. It's looked pretty cool so we decided to give it a go. When we walk in there is no host to greet us. It seemed really busy and short staffed. We looked for someone to explained the seating process. A server eventually came over, sat us and walked away. Still no greeting, no menus, no water, Nothing at all. We remained patient because we were all hungry and didn't want to search for another place. We chalked it up to them being really busy with only two servers. A server finally came by, handed us one menu(for 6 people) and walked away. Still no greeting or explanation. She returned 15 mins later with additional menus and walked away again. After waiting yet again another server named Deandre came by to take our orders. We waited roughly 30 minutes for our food to come out with no apology for the delay or any refills on our water.  When our food finally came, it was sub-par at best. Half of our food was lukewarm. Two people ordered the Fish & Chips. The Fish was heavily breaded and mushy and the fries looked like they were the crumbs at the bottom of the bag. I ordered a Mac and cheese and a side salad. The mac was a 4 out of ten. The salad was sauggy, and had nothing in it but lettuce and dressing.  Another person ordered the mushroom flatbread and Mac and cheese.  The flatbread was cold and wet. We asked for a manager and she came with no apology or solution to rectify the situation. She preoceeded to tell us no one has ever complained to her before and offered us shots(really?). We declined and then she offered us dessert(really lady). We asked her kindly for our check so we could leave. All we wanted was a simple apology and some sort of solution. We were not looking for our meals to be comped. We were patrons who were dissatisfied and was looking for resolve.
